Engineering Manager
Responsibilities
The incumbent will be responsible to manage and coordinate all engineering services to support Production and GA Departments.  The services will be in Mechanical, Electrical & Civil areas which consist of routine preventive maintenance, projects, trouble shooting, analyze technology for continuous improvement & efficiency, plant improvement, and cooperation with GA Dept related to building projects.Requirements : MaleMaximum age 45 years oldMin Bachelor Degree in Electrical/Mechanical/Mechatronic Engineering from reputable universityProficient in English, both written & oralExperience : min 5 yrs as Assistant of Engineering Manager or 3 yrs as Engineering ManagerKnowledge in hydraulic, valves, pneumatics, PLC systemKnowledge in quality management including ISO, safety, Kaizen, 5S practice in house keeping and continuous improvementStrong leadership, good team work, analytical, problem solver & managerial skillAgree to be placed in Pulogadung  If you meet our qualification please send your Resume + Latest Photograph
